# One Nabil, One Trust - Strategic Brand Unification Presentation

This repository contains an interactive, visually-rich HTML presentation for the **"One Nabil, One Trust"** strategic brand unification plan. The presentation is designed to communicate the vision, strategy, market analysis, implementation roadmap, and expected impacts of unifying the Nabil brands into a single, powerful entity.

## Features

- **20 Dynamic Slides**: Covers situation analysis, market insights, branding strategy, campaign ideas, digital and retail plans, stakeholder engagement, risk analysis, KPIs, and more.
- **Interactive Navigation**: Easily move between slides with previous/next buttons, with a live slide counter.
- **Infographics & Metrics**: Visualizes key data and ideas using modern infographics and metric cards.
- **Animated Charts**: Powered by [Chart.js](https://www.chartjs.org/), with unique charts for market dynamics, ROI, risk, and more.
- **Modern Design**: Stylish, mobile-friendly layout with gradients, blur effects, and responsive grids.

## Getting Started

1. **Clone the Repository**
    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/meheduz/Case.git
    cd Case
    ```

2. **Open the Presentation**
    - Simply open `case.html` in your web browser.
    - No build steps or dependencies required.

3. **Navigate Slides**
    - Use the "Next" and "Previous" buttons at the bottom to move through the presentation.
    - The slide counter at the top right shows your current position.

## File Structure

```
Case/
├── case.html        # Main presentation file (all code and styles embedded)
├── README.md        # This readme file
```

## Customization

- **Content**: To update text, metrics, or branding, edit the relevant HTML in `case.html`.
- **Charts**: Chart data and types can be changed in the `<script>` section at the bottom of `case.html`.
- **Styling**: All CSS is included in a `<style>` block in the HTML head. Modify for your brand colors, fonts, etc.

## Dependencies

- [Chart.js 3.9.1](https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/3.9.1/chart.min.js) (loaded via CDN)

